------------
Containers
--------------------
These are the most basic layout element in bootstrap and are required when using the grid system.
Containers are used to wrap content with some padding.

Different types of containers
-----------------------------------------
.container - which has max-width at each responsive breakpoint.

.container-fluid - which has 100% width at all breakpoints.


.container-sm (small)
.container-md (medium)
.container-lg (large)
.container-xl
.container-xxl


<html>
<head>
<title>Bootstrap</title>
<link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet" integrity="sha384-QWTKZyjpPEjISv5WaRU9OFeRpok6YctnYmDr5pNlyT2bRjXh0JMhjY6hW+ALEwIH" crossorigin="anonymous">
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js" integrity="sha384-YvpcrYf0tY3lHB60NNkmXc5s9fDVZLESaAA55NDzOxhy9GkcIdslK1eN7N6jIeHz" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
</head>
<body>
<div class="container">
<h1>This is heading1</h1>
<h2>This is heading2</h2>
</div>

<div class="container-fluid">
<h1>This is heading1</h1>
<h2>This is heading2</h2>

</div>
<div class="container-sm bg-dark text-white p-5 m-5">
<h1>This is heading1 small container</h1>
<h2>This is heading2</h2>

</div>
<div class="container-md bg-light ">
<h1>This is heading1 medium container</h1>
<h2>This is heading2</h2>

</div>
<div class="container-lg border bg-primary">
<h1>This is heading1 large container</h1>
<h2>This is heading2</h2>

</div>
</body>
</html>

